---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="BMI Calculator for India (2026) – Indian BMI Chart & Healthy Weight Range"
  description="Calculate your BMI with specific Indian/Asian thresholds. Check healthy weight and metabolic risks."
  keywords="bmi calculator india, bmi chart india, ideal weight for indian, asian bmi calculator, indian weight standards"
  canonicalUrl="https://calbmi.com/bmi-calculator-india.html"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "CalBmi - BMI Calculator for India",
      "url": "https://calbmi.com/bmi-calculator-india.html",
      "description": "Calculate Body Mass Index (BMI) using specific Indian/Asian thresholds.",
      "applicationCategory": "HealthApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires HTML5.",
      "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0.00", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
      "aggregateRating": {
        "@type": "AggregateRating",
        "ratingValue": "4.9",
        "ratingCount": "112",
        "bestRating": "5",
        "worstRating": "1"
      }
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Calculator Section -->
  <section id="calculator" class="calc-section" style="padding-top:2.5rem">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bmi-page-header scroll-reveal">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
          Home
        </a>
        <div class="bmi-page-title-block">
          <span class="hero-badge" style="margin:0">
            🇮🇳 India / Asian Thresholds
          </span>
          <h1 class="bmi-page-title">BMI Calculator <span class="hero-gradient">for India</span></h1>
        </div>
        <p class="bmi-page-sub">Analyze your Body Mass Index using the WHO Asia-Pacific standards for South Asians.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="calc-grid">
        <!-- Input Card -->
        <div class="card calc-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="card-title">Enter Your Details</h2>
            <p class="card-subtitle">Fill in your measurements below</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Unit Toggle -->
          <div class="unit-toggle-group" role="group" aria-label="Unit system">
            <button class="unit-btn active" id="btnMetric" data-unit="metric" onclick="setUnit('metric')">Metric</button>
            <button class="unit-btn" id="btnImperial" data-unit="imperial" onclick="setUnit('imperial')">Imperial</button>
          </div>

          <form id="bmiForm" class="bmi-form" novalidate>
            <!-- Age -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label" for="ageInput">Age <span class="label-hint">(2 – 120 years)</span></label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="ageInput" placeholder="e.g. 25" min="2" max="120" />
                <span class="input-unit">yrs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="ageError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Gender -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Gender</label>
              <div class="gender-group">
                <label class="gender-option" id="genderMaleLabel">
                  <input type="radio" name="gender" value="male" id="genderMale" checked />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                    Male
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="gender-option" id="genderFemaleLabel">
                  <input type="radio" name="gender" value="female" id="genderFemale" />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/><path d="M9 20h6"/></svg>
                    Female
                  </span>
                </label>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height (Metric) -->
            <div class="form-group" id="heightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="heightCm">Height</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20M4 6l3 3M4 12h4M4 18l3-3M20 6l-3 3M20 12h-4M20 18l-3-3"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightCm" placeholder="e.g. 170" min="50" max="280" />
                <span class="input-unit">cm</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="heightCmError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height (Imperial) -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="heightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label">Height</label>
              <div class="imperial-row">
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20"/></svg>
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightFt" placeholder="5" min="1" max="9" />
                  <span class="input-unit">ft</span>
                </div>
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="heightIn" placeholder="7" min="0" max="11" />
                  <span class="input-unit">in</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="heightImperialError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight (Metric) -->
            <div class="form-group" id="weightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="weightKg">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="weightKg" placeholder="e.g. 68" min="2" max="600" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">kg</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="weightKgError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight (Imperial) -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="weightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="weightLbs">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="weightLbs" placeholder="e.g. 150" min="5" max="1300" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">lbs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="weightLbsError"></div>
            </div>

            <button type="submit" class="calc-btn" id="calcBtn">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
              Calculate BMI
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="reset-btn" id="resetBtn" onclick="resetForm()">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 0 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 0-6.74 2.74L3 8"/><path d="M3 3v5h5"/></svg>
              Reset
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>

        <!-- Result Card -->
        <div class="card result-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.15s" id="resultCard">
          <div class="result-placeholder" id="resultPlaceholder">
            <div class="placeholder-icon">
              <svg width="64" height="64" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
                <path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="placeholder-text">Enter your details and click <strong>Calculate BMI</strong> to see your results</p>
          </div>

          <div class="result-content hidden" id="resultContent">
            <!-- Gauge -->
            <div class="gauge-container">
              <svg class="gauge-svg" viewBox="0 0 220 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <defs>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeUnderweight" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#60a5fa"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#3b82f6"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeNormal" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#34d399"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#10b981"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeOverweight" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#fbbf24"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#f59e0b"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <linearGradient id="gaugeObese" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#f87171"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#ef4444"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                  <filter id="gaugeShadow">
                    <feDropShadow dx="0" dy="2" stdDeviation="3" flood-color="rgba(0,0,0,0.2)"/>
                  </filter>
                </defs>

                <!-- Background arcs -->
                <path d="M 20 115 A 90 90 0 0 1 57.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeUnderweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 57.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 110 25" stroke="url(#gaugeNormal)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 110 25 A 90 90 0 0 1 162.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeOverweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>
                <path d="M 162.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 200 115" stroke="url(#gaugeObese)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3"/>

                <!-- Active arcs -->
                <path id="arcUnderweight" d="M 20 115 A 90 90 0 0 1 57.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeUnderweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcNormal" d="M 57.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 110 25" stroke="url(#gaugeNormal)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcOverweight" d="M 110 25 A 90 90 0 0 1 162.5 36.4" stroke="url(#gaugeOverweight)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>
                <path id="arcObese" d="M 162.5 36.4 A 90 90 0 0 1 200 115" stroke="url(#gaugeObese)" stroke-width="18" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0" class="arc-segment"/>

                <!-- Needle -->
                <g id="gaugeNeedle" transform="rotate(0, 110, 115)">
                  <line x1="110" y1="115" x2="110" y2="40" stroke="var(--foreground)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" filter="url(#gaugeShadow)"/>
                  <circle cx="110" cy="115" r="7" fill="var(--foreground)" filter="url(#gaugeShadow)"/>
                  <circle cx="110" cy="115" r="4" fill="var(--background)"/>
                </g>

                <!-- BMI Value -->
                <text id="gaugeBmiValue" x="110" y="95" text-anchor="middle" class="gauge-value-text" font-size="22" font-weight="800" fill="var(--foreground)">–</text>
                <text x="110" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="var(--muted-foreground)" font-weight="500">BMI</text>

                <!-- Labels -->
                <text x="10" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#3b82f6" font-weight="600">Under</text>
                <text x="65" y="28" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#10b981" font-weight="600">Normal</text>
                <text x="157" y="28" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#f59e0b" font-weight="600">Over</text>
                <text x="210" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#ef4444" font-weight="600">Obese</text>
              </svg>
            </div>

            <!-- Category Badge -->
            <div class="category-badge-container">
              <div class="category-badge" id="categoryBadge">
                <span id="categoryIcon"></span>
                <span id="categoryText">–</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Stats Grid -->
            <div class="stats-grid">
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Your BMI</div>
                <div class="stat-value" id="statBmi">–</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Healthy Range</div>
                <div class="stat-value stat-small" id="statRange">18.5–22.9</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">Ideal Weight</div>
                <div class="stat-value stat-small" id="statIdeal">–</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-item">
                <div class="stat-label">BMI Prime</div>
                <div class="stat-value" id="statPrime">–</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Health message -->
            <div class="health-message" id="healthMessage"></div>

            <!-- Weight to Lose/Gain -->
            <div class="weight-diff" id="weightDiff"></div>

            <!-- Indian specific notice -->
            <div style="background:var(--muted); padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; font-size:0.775rem; color:var(--muted-foreground); margin-top:1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--brand-primary)">
              <strong>South Asian Notice:</strong> South Asians have a higher body fat % and abdominal fat at lower BMIs. Indian medical guidelines recommend aiming for a BMI between 18.5 and 22.9.
            </div>

            <!-- Calories CTA -->
            <div class="calories-cta" id="caloriesCta">
              <div class="cta-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2a7 7 0 0 1 7 7c0 5-7 13-7 13S5 14 5 9a7 7 0 0 1 7-7z"/><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="cta-body">
                <p class="cta-title">Daily calories for Indians?</p>
                <p class="cta-sub">Find out your calorie target based on dietary preferences and activity level.</p>
              </div>
              <a href="calories.html" class="cta-btn" id="ctaBtn">
                Calculate
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- BMI Classification Table -->
      <div class="card table-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s" id="tableCard">
        <h3 class="section-title">Indian (South Asian) BMI Classification Table</h3>
        <p class="card-subtitle" style="margin-bottom:1rem">According to the Consensus Guidelines for Indian Adults (WHO Asia-Pacific guidelines)</p>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table class="bmi-table" id="bmiTable">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Category</th>
                <th>BMI Range</th>
                <th>Health Risk Threshold</th>
                <th>Status</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#3b82f6"></span> Underweight</td>
                <td>&lt; 18.5</td>
                <td>Nutritional deficiency risk</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-moderate">Moderate</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#10b981"></span> Normal Weight</td>
                <td>18.5 – 22.9</td>
                <td>Low risk (Healthy Range)</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-low">Low</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#f59e0b"></span> Overweight</td>
                <td>23.0 – 24.9</td>
                <td>Increased metabolic risk</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-elevated">Elevated</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="table-row">
                <td><span class="category-dot" style="background:#ef4444"></span> Obese</td>
                <td>&ge; 25.0</td>
                <td>High risk for diabetes & heart disease</td>
                <td><span class="risk-badge risk-high">High</span></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Demographic SEO Article -->
  <section class="landing-article">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="landing-article-inner scroll-reveal">
        <h2>The Complete Indian Guide to BMI (Body Mass Index) & Asian Thresholds</h2>
        <p>In global health and clinical research, it has become increasingly clear that a "one size fits all" approach to medical diagnostics does not work. This is particularly true for the **Body Mass Index (BMI)**. While Western countries use standard WHO guidelines where a BMI of 25 is classified as overweight and 30 as obese, clinical research has proven that South Asians—particularly the **Indian population**—face high metabolic risks at much lower weight levels. As a result, the Indian Ministry of Health and the WHO Asia-Pacific Guidelines established a lower weight standard specifically for South Asian adults. This guide explains why Indian BMI guidelines are different, how to calculate your score, and practical dietary advice.</p>

        <h3>Why does India have lower BMI thresholds?</h3>
        <p>South Asians have a unique body composition phenotype, sometimes referred to as the **"Thin-Fat Phenotype."** Even if an Indian individual looks relatively lean from the outside (with a standard BMI of 23 or 24), they typically carry a **higher percentage of body fat**—especially visceral fat stored in the abdominal cavity—and less skeletal muscle mass than Caucasians of the same age, gender, and BMI.</p>
        <p>This excess abdominal fat is metabolically dangerous. It releases inflammatory fatty acids directly into the portal vein leading to the liver, causing early liver fat accumulation, hyperinsulinemia, and cardiovascular inflammation. Studies have demonstrated that South Asians experience elevated rates of cardiovascular disease, insulin resistance, and Type 2 diabetes at a BMI score where Westerners are considered healthy. For this reason, the healthy BMI cutoff for Indian adults is lowered to **18.5 – 22.9**.</p>

        <h3>Comparison of Indian vs. Global BMI Standards</h3>
        <p>The differences between the standard international thresholds and the Indian Consensus guidelines are significant:</p>
        
        <table class="ref-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Classification</th>
              <th>Global WHO Range</th>
              <th>Indian (South Asian) Range</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Underweight</strong></td>
              <td>Less than 18.5</td>
              <td>Less than 18.5</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Normal Weight</strong></td>
              <td>18.5 – 24.9</td>
              <td>18.5 – 22.9</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Overweight</strong></td>
              <td>25.0 – 29.9</td>
              <td>23.0 – 24.9</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Obese</strong></td>
              <td>30.0 and above</td>
              <td>25.0 and above</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Susceptibility to Metabolic Syndrome in South Asians</h3>
        <p>The revised thresholds exist primarily to screen for **Metabolic Syndrome**, a cluster of conditions that increase the risk of heart disease, stroke, and diabetes. Indians have a genetic predisposition (partially due to evolutionary adaptations to famine) that promotes fat accumulation in abdominal reserves. When an Indian adult's BMI exceeds **23**, their risk of developing:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Type 2 Diabetes:</strong> South Asians develop diabetes 5 to 10 years earlier on average than other ethnic groups.</li>
          <li><strong>Dyslipidemia:</strong> Characterized by high triglycerides, elevated LDL ("bad") cholesterol, and low HDL ("good") cholesterol.</li>
          <li><strong>Premature Heart Disease:</strong> Indians account for roughly 60% of the world's heart disease burden, often experiencing cardiac events in their 30s and 40s.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Indian Height & Healthy Weight Reference Chart</h3>
        <p>Based on the Indian healthy BMI range (18.5 to 22.9), here are the target weight ranges for common Indian heights:</p>
        
        <table class="ref-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Height (Metric / Imperial)</th>
              <th>Standard Healthy Range</th>
              <th>Indian Healthy Range (18.5 - 22.9)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>150 cm (4'11")</td>
              <td>41.6 – 56.0 kg</td>
              <td>41.6 – 51.5 kg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>155 cm (5'1")</td>
              <td>44.4 – 59.8 kg</td>
              <td>44.4 – 55.0 kg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>160 cm (5'3")</td>
              <td>47.4 – 63.7 kg</td>
              <td>47.4 – 58.6 kg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>165 cm (5'5")</td>
              <td>50.4 – 67.8 kg</td>
              <td>50.4 – 62.3 kg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>170 cm (5'7")</td>
              <td>53.5 – 72.0 kg</td>
              <td>53.5 – 66.2 kg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>175 cm (5'9")</td>
              <td>56.7 – 76.3 kg</td>
              <td>56.7 – 70.1 kg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>180 cm (5'11")</td>
              <td>59.9 – 80.7 kg</td>
              <td>59.9 – 74.2 kg</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Dietary Tips for Maintaining a Healthy BMI in India</h3>
        <p>Traditional Indian diets are rich in grains, but modern urban lifestyles have led to high consumption of refined carbohydrates, trans-fats, and sugar. To maintain a healthy BMI:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Manage Carbohydrate Portions:</strong> A typical Indian plate features large portions of white rice, roti, or naan, with minimal vegetables and protein. Reduce rice and wheat portions, replacing them with complex grains like ragi, jowar, bajra, or brown rice.</li>
          <li><strong>Increase Protein Intake:</strong> Protein deficiency is widespread in India, especially among vegetarians. Increase protein by consuming paneer, tofu, dal, sprouts, Greek yogurt, eggs, chicken, and fish. Aim for 1.2 to 1.6 grams of protein per kilogram of body weight.</li>
          <li><strong>Limit Deep-Fried Snacks:</strong> Avoid frequent samosas, pakoras, and sev. Replace deep-fried snacks with roasted makhana, unsalted nuts, or boiled chana.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>To learn more about your metabolism, check your resting calories using the <a href="/bmr.html">BMR Calculator</a>, estimate your daily energy expenditure with the <a href="/tdee.html">TDEE Calculator</a>, or plan a balanced diet using the <a href="/macro.html">Macro Calculator</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Script -->
  <script src="/app.js" is:inline></script>
</Layout>
